post_text: We're celebrating our 20th ANNIVERSARY! Established in 2000, Lift For Life Academy was the VERY FIRST charter school in St. Louis. LFLA has grown in so many ways. We now have over 750 students, a sprawling campus with a recently added gym and elementary school, a progressive and relevant curriculum, and a staff that nurtures and supports each and every student. We're excited and inspired to be in our 20th year with more visions and dreams to come!

RENTAL/MORTGAGE Assistance Program
$5.4 million dollars of the City of St. Louis' CARES Act funding is allocated to assist City residents with their rental & mortgage payments. The Department of Human Services in collaboration with the Affordable Housing Commission and various housing organizations have established a rental and mortgage assistance program to help residents who are experiencing financial hardship during the COVID-19 pandemic. All forms of assistance will be made directly to the landlord/lender. Applications may be made online, by email, or by calling 314-657-1650 to ask that an application be mailed to you or sent via email. https://www.stlouis-mo.gov/government/departments/human-services/cares-act-rental-mortgage-assistance.cfm

post_text:
Why & How to Wear & Handle your Face Mask per CDC:

Wear a Face Covering to Protect Others

Wear a face covering that covers your nose and mouth to help protect others in case you’re infected with COVID-19 but don’t have symptoms

Wear a face covering in public settings when around people who don’t live in your household, especially when it may be difficult for you to stay six feet apart

Wear a face covering correctly for maximum protection

Don’t put the face covering around your neck or up on your forehead

Don’t touch the face covering, and, if you do, wash your hands or use hand sanitizer to disinfect

Untie the strings behind your head or stretch the ear loops

Handle only by the ear loops or ties

Fold outside corners together and place covering in the washing machine

Be careful not to touch your eyes, nose, and mouth when removing and wash hands immediately after removing

Don't forget! There's still a few days left to apply for the Pandemic-EBT. Deadline is June 30, 2020
Under the Families First Coronavirus Response Act of 2020, families that qualify for free or reduced price meals at school may be eligible for a new one-time Pandemic Electronic Benefits Transfer (P-EBT) of up to $302 per child (PK-12) to help cover the cost of meals students have eaten at home on days that schools have been closed.
Lift For Life Academy does not certify families for P-EBT. For any questions, please contact the Department of Social Services (DSS) directly through the online chat feature at mydss.mo.gov or call 855-373-4636. For more information on the EBT card, visit: mydss.mo.gov/food-assistance/ebt.

Please know that we are currently developing a safe and thoughtful plan for re-opening Lift For Life Academy for the coming school year. We will be sharing the details of the plan in the next few weeks to ensure that you are well aware of expectations and policies. Thank you for your patience and please be safe and healthy!

Warmest regards,
Dr. Katrice Noble
Deputy Director

Attention all LFLA families!
Pandemic-EBT: Deadline to Apply is June 30, 2020
Under the Families First Coronavirus Response Act of 2020, families that qualify for free or reduced price meals at school may be eligible for a new one-time Pandemic Electronic Benefits Transfer (P-EBT) of up to $302 per child (PK-12) to help cover the cost of meals students have eaten at home on days that schools have been closed.
Lift For Life Academy does not certify families for P-EBT. For any questions, please contact the Department of Social Services (DSS) directly through the online chat feature at mydss.mo.gov or call 855-373-4636. For more information on the EBT card, visit: mydss.mo.gov/food-assistance/ebt.

shared_text:
Amy Schmitt is with Wanda Love and 7 others.
June 4 at 10:28 PM ·

Tonight we celebrated the class of 2020 and it was unforgettable! High school students dream to walk across the stage in front of their family, peers, and teachers and unfortunately that couldn’t happen for the class of 2020. But in true LFLA fashion... we made it happen so that students COULD “walk across a stage” in a very unique drive thru graduation! I am so proud to be a teacher of these wonderful seniors and that they allowed me to be a part of their journey. When this group of kids were freshmen the teachers always said, “this class will make history”, and wouldn’t you know it.... THEY DID! Congratulations ￼ ￼ class of 2020!!!#classof2020 #LFLA #HawkPride

post_text:
LFLA OFFERS PRE-K in both NORTH and SOUTH LOCATIONS!
Give your child an educational boost by enrolling them in LFLA’s Pre-K program. Each day children take part in carefully planned experiences that promote their interest and growth in literacy, art, mathematics, science, social studies, music and movement. Your child will develop the foundation they need to lead the way in Kindergarten versus falling behind.

The two locations are Southside Early Childhood Center, 2101 S. Jefferson, 63104 and Beginning Futures, 4981 Thrush Avenue, 63120.

To register your 4 – 5 year old, complete the enrollment application on our website, liftforlifeacademy.org. Questions? Contact Dr. Katrice Noble at k.noble@liftforlifeacademy.org.

Photo: Brittany Jones and her daughter, Lillie, our first enrolled Pre-K student.

post_text:
A loving and hopeful message from our leader, Dr. Noble:

I am in awe of what we have established at Lift For Life Academy. Just like we knew that we couldn't stop the gun violence, we can't stop the massive racism that plagues this world. We have to be the difference makers and the change agents. What we can do is make small changes within ourselves and with our families in order to begin the process of changing the world! I am but hopeful!

post_text: Well our amazing secret is out of the bag! We are expanding to Pre-k! 🏆
shared_text:
Southeast News
May 15 at 4:02 PM ·

The Southeast Missouri State University Board of Regents today approved an amendment to the charter of the Lift For Life Academy in St. Louis, Missouri, to expand the school’s services to include pre-kindergarten. The Lift for Life Academy currently serves students in kindergarten through 12th grade. The amendment would add pre-kindergarten services as part of a St. Louis area charter school Early Childhood Education Cooperative. https://bit.ly/3cBy1AT

post_text: During these strange times, there are many expressions of kindness and compassion that give us hope for the future. One example is ... our staff partnering with the St. Louis Area Food Bank to provide food pickup day to our students and families last Wednesday.
